The paper deals with interpretability and transparency in Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for image analysis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of multiple Semantically Interpretable Activation Maps (SIAM) to provide insight into what the model has seen and where, which is related to explainability and interpretability in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method also involves linearly combining attribute maps to produce the final output, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper uses the SUN Attributes database to extract 33 attributes for the task of landscape scenicness estimation, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
